Subject: Flush (cards) 
To: Stephanie
Content:
A flush is a hand of playing cards where all cards are of the same suit. The general meaning of the word flush is fullness or abundance, as there are similar meaning words in Dutch, French, Italian and Spanish. The words origin is 'fluxus' in Latin, which means 'flow'.
I read the paragraph on http://wikipedia.org
